"```sql\nSELECT c.position\nFROM results r\nJOIN drivers d ON r.driverId = d.driverId\nJOIN races ra ON r.raceId = ra.raceId\nJOIN circuits c ON ra.circuitId = c.circuitId\nWHERE d.forename = 'Lewis' AND d.surname = 'Hamilton'\nAND r.fastestLapTime = (\n    SELECT MIN(fastestLapTime)\n    FROM results r2\n    WHERE r2.driverId = d.driverId\n);\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the position of the circuits during Lewis Hamilton's fastest lap in a Formula 1 race. It joins the `results`, `drivers`, `races`, and `circuits` tables to find the relevant data, filtering for Lewis Hamilton and selecting the minimum fastest lap time."